# ATS Resume Analyzer

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.9-blue)
![Django](https://img.shields.io/badge/Django-4.2-green)
![Django REST Framework](https://img.shields.io/badge/Django%20REST%20Framework-DRF-red)
![SQLite](https://img.shields.io/badge/Database-SQLite-blue)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Educational-lightgrey)

## Overview

ATS Resume Analyzer is a Django-based web application that helps job seekers evaluate their resumes using an Applicant Tracking System (ATS) approach.

The application allows users to register, log in securely, upload resumes in PDF format, automatically extract resume text and technical skills, calculate an ATS score, compare resumes against a job description, and manage uploaded resumes through a personalized dashboard.

This project demonstrates full-stack web development using Django, Django REST Framework, SQLite, HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap.

---

## Features

- User Registration & Login Authentication
- Secure User Dashboard
- Upload Resume (PDF)
- Automatic Resume Text Extraction
- Technical Skill Extraction
- ATS Score Calculation
- Resume vs Job Description Match Score
- View Uploaded Resumes
- Resume Details Page
- SQLite Database Integration

---

